{{zh-forms|[[金屋]][[藏]][[娇]]|[[金屋藏嬌]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
Literally: [[to]] [[keep]] [[a]] [[beauty]] (inside one's) [[golden]] [[house]]
*[[w:Emperor Wu of Han|Emperor Wu of Han]] kept his cousin, the [[w:Empress Chen Jiao|Empress Chen Jiao]], as a wife in a golden house.  Later, this became a metaphor for keeping a mistress or a young wife in a luxurious house or apartment.

===Idiom===
{{PAGENAME}} (''[[Pinyin]]'' [[jīnwū]] [[cáng]] [[jiāo]])

# to take a [[concubine]]
# to keep a [[mistress]] in a [[tuck]]ed [[away]] in a [[luxurious]] [[house]] or [[apartment]]

===Synonyms===
*[[金屋贮娇]]

